{
  "stem": "321.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That's all I knew, a few English words.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now be quiet, go to sleep, sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she screamed even louder.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then I bent down, and the towel fell off.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she started calming down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She didn't recognize me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I cuddled her, and then I told her a German story, and she fell asleep.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] But I remember being sent to school right after Christmas in the new year, 1939, and being in the English school and having difficulty.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But I learned.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I wrote letters to my mother in Germany that mailboxes are-- are blue here in England, and you know, that sort of thing, you can-- this is different and this is different, in German.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But by the time the spring semester came, I used, as I call it, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I spoke and wrote English pretty well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It's unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I have the letters, so I can prove, you know, that the language was learned very quickly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But getting used to a different way of life and people feeling sorry for you and pitying you and looking down on you as the refugee, it was tough.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Now, I didn't see the-- you know, I didn't see my cousins very much, nor my brother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So it was isolation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She stayed behind.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Visa was refused something like 11 times, until my father's partner went to the foreign office in London to see the original application.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He insisted on that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what had happened, my father's English wasn't that good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He put a tick in the wrong box, were you ever a Communist or some-- I don't even know the details.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
